<h2>Add TinyMCE Configuration</h2>
<form action="manage_addZTinyConfiguration">

<dl>

  <dt><label for="id">Id:</label></dt>
  <dd><input name="id" size="30" value="tinymce.conf" /></dd>

  <dt><label for="title">Title:</label></dt>
  <dd><input name="title" size="30" value="My TinyMCE configuration" /></dd>
  
  <dt><label for="optimize">Optimize:</label></dt>
  <dd><input type="checkbox" name="optimize" id="optimize" value="1" checked="checked" /></dd>
  
<textarea name="configuration" style="display:none">//Sample stuff to get you started
mode : "textareas",
theme : "simple"</textarea>
</dl>
<br />
<input type="submit" value=" Add " />
<input type="submit" name="addandedit" value="Add and Edit" />
</form> 

<p><b>Help:</b><br />
A TinyMCE Configuration is a little object that works together with a <code>ZTinyMCE</code>
instance to render the TinyMCE widget. You can have one ZTinyMCE instance (one is enough)
and several TinyMCE configurations depending on how you want to use TinyMCE.<br />
The configuration is simply a chunk JavaScript code that sets the option for the widget 
you want to employ.
</p>

